      <h1 style="font-size:2.25rem;margin-top:1rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem">Wet/Dry Vacs for Contractors: 10 Models Compared on Suction, Durability, and Filtration</h1>
      <div style="color:#64748b;font-size:0.9rem">June 17, 2026 · 11 min read</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>A wet/dry shop vac is the backbone of job site cleanup. Whether you're sucking up drywall dust after a demo, draining a flooded basement, or connecting it to your miter saw for dust extraction, the right vacuum saves hours every single week.</p>
      <p>But with dozens of models on Amazon and specs that range from 4 HP to 6.5 HP and tanks from 6 to 16 gallons, it's hard to compare them at a glance. We've gathered 8 of the top-rated wet/dry shop vacs for contractors and compared them side by side — by power, capacity, noise level, filtration, and real-world contractor reviews.</p>

      <h2>Comparison Methodology</h2>
      <p>Every vac on this list was evaluated based on: verified buyer ratings, peak horsepower, tank capacity (gallons or liters), filter type, included accessories, noise level, and value at its current price point. All links go directly to Amazon for current pricing and availability — prices change frequently.</p>

      <h2>1. DEWALT DXV06P 6 Gallon — Best Compact (4.7★)</h2>
      <p><strong>ASIN:</strong> B07BY8BZ3K</p>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07BY8BZ3K?tag=sciencesolved-20" rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank">DEWALT DXV06P 6 Gallon Wet/Dry Vac</a> earns the highest rating in our lineup at 4.7 stars. With 4 peak HP and a compact 6-gallon tank, it's the perfect size for individual contractors who need to carry their vac up stairs and through tight spaces. It includes a blower function for clearing debris from awkward corners.</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Electricians, plumbers, HVAC techs, finish carpenters.</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07BY8BZ3K?tag=sciencesolved-20" rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank">Check current price on Amazon</a></p>

      <h2>2. DEWALT DXV16PA 16 Gallon — Best Large Capacity (4.7★)</h2>
      <p><strong>ASIN:</strong> B07CBC64DR</p>
      <p>Tied for the top rating at 4.7 stars, the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07CBC64DR?tag=sciencesolved-20" rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank">DEWALT DXV16PA 16 Gallon 6.5 HP</a> is built for serious jobsite cleanup. This is the vacuum you want on a large construction site — the 16-gallon tank means you can go all day without stopping to empty it, and 6.5 peak HP provides maximum suction for wet pickup, heavy debris, and dust extraction.</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> General contractors, framing crews, renovation teams, large job sites.</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07CBC64DR?tag=sciencesolved-20" rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank">Check current price on Amazon</a></p>

      <h2>3. DEWALT 9 Gallon DXV09PZ — Best All-Around (4.6★)</h2>
      <p><strong>ASIN:</strong> B09V7KDV69</p>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09V7KDV69?tag=sciencesolved-20" rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank">DEWALT 9 Gallon Poly Wet/Dry Vac DXV09PZ</a> hits the sweet spot. At 9 gallons, it's large enough for serious work shifts but compact enough to fit in a truck bed or van without dominating your workspace. The poly tank is lightweight, rust-proof, and durable. A favorite among contractors who need one vac that does everything reasonably well.</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> All-purpose jobsite use, medium-size projects.</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09V7KDV69?tag=sciencesolved-20" rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank">Check current price on Amazon</a></p>

